The '''Federal Register of Legislation''' (formerly '''ComLaw'''), also known as the '''Legislation Register''',  is an [[Australian]] [[Government of Australia|government]] [[web site]] run by the [[Office of Parliamentary Counsel]] since October 2012 that provides online copies of Commonwealth legislation and related documents. The website was redesigned and re-released early in 2011. {{as of|2016}} ComLaw links redirect to the '''Federal Register of Legislation''' site.

