In September 2018, 5 banks, including [[BBVA]], structured a revolving credit facility (RCF) for the Italian power utility A2A in a finance deal valued at €400 million euros. The syndicated loan avails itself of a margin mechanism based on two parameters: the performance of two selected KPIs (waste processing capacity and the volume of renewable energy sold in the wholesale market, emphasizing the focus of the A2A Group on the circular economy and decarbonation). The solicited ESG Rating is provided annually by [[Standard Ethics Aei]].<ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.bbva.com/en/bbva-signs-new-sustainable-loan-italy-a2a/ </ref><ref>{{cite news |url=https://www.eticanews.it/in-breve/un-altro-sustainable-loan-per-le-utility-italiane-tocca-ad-a2a/</ref>
