The '''Institute for Public Affairs''' ({{lang-sk|Inštitút pre verejné otázky, IVO}}) is a [[Non-governmental organization|non-governmental]] [[think tank]], registered to operate in the [[Slovakia|Slovak Republic]]. It was founded by [[Grigorij Mesežnikov]] and [[Martin Bútora]], with the aim of promoting the values of an open society and a democratic political culture in public policy and decision-making. IVO brings together experts from many different areas of study. Mesežnikov has been President of the institute since 1998.

