{{Expand Portuguese|Ternuma|date=November 2018}}

'''Ternuma''' (Portuguese [[wiktionary:acronym|acronym]] for ''Terrorism Never More'') is a [[Brazil]]ian [[Non-governmental organization|nongovernmental organization]] formed in 1998 by the [[Brazilian Army]], military reserve force, family members and sympathizers with the purpose of [[Historical revisionism|reinterpret the history]] of the [[Military dictatorship in Brazil|military regime that ruled Brazil from 1964 to 1985]].<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Santos|first=Rocha, Luzimary dos|date=26 May 2016|title=Ditadura, memória e justiça : “revolução” e golpe de 1964 transitam no ciberespaço|url=https://ri.ufs.br/jspui/handle/riufs/5652|access-date=19 November 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.snh2017.anpuh.org/resources/anais/54/1502825167_ARQUIVO_OTRABALHOCOMMEMORIASNOENSINODEHISTORIADADITADURAMILITARNOBRASIL(COMPLETO).pdf|title=O Trabalho com Memórias no Ensino de História da Ditadura Militar no Brasil|last=Rigotto Genari|first=Elton|website=XXIX Simpósio Nacional de História|archive-url=|archive-date=|dead-url=|access-date=19 November 2018}}</ref> It praises the [[1964 Brazilian coup d'état|Brazilian coup d'état]] and strongly criticizes the private property intrusions promoted by the [[Landless Workers' Movement]].<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.cartamaior.com.br/?/Editoria/Midia/Carta-Maior-interpela-Folha-na-Justica/12/32467|title=Carta Maior irá processar a Folha de São Paulo|work=Carta Maior|access-date=19 November 2018|language=pt-br}}</ref>

